data.text:
September 07, 1914 was a Monday and it was the 250th day of the year 1914 in the Gregorian calendar.

September 07, 1914 can also be written as 9/7/1914 in the US and as 7/9/1914 in UK and Europe.

The Zodiac and Astrological sign for September 7th is Virgo.

Virgo is the 6th sign in the Western Zodiac. People born between August 23rd and September 22nd belong to the Virgo sign: discover Virgo personality and who should a Virgo marry.

Moon phase

The moon phase on September 07, 1914 was Waning gibbous.

The moon phase refers to the appearance of the Moon in the night sky on September 07, 1914 and is determined by the portion of the Moon's illuminated surface that is visible from Earth.

An observer located in New York City on September 07, 1914 at 10pm, would see the moon, being 85% full, rising at 07:25 pm and setting at 09:26 am.

The previous full moon was on Sep 04, 1914 while the next full moon would come on Oct 04, 1914.

What is special about September 7th?

September 7th refers to a specific date on the calendar, which is the 7th day of the month of September. It is a date that occurs annually and is part of the Gregorian calendar, which is widely used around the world.

Over the years several events happened on September 7th, such as:

2018 - Syrian civil war: presidents of russia, iran and russia disagree with the turkish president's proposal for a ceasefire at idlib following a meeting in tehran. this would not include islamist militants that these nations seek to defeat.

2017 - Israeli involvement in the syrian civil war. it is believed that israeli jets attacked a military research center near masyaf in hama governorate. at least two soldiers from the syrian army were killed. rumours claimed that the facility contained chemical weapons.

2016 - Syrian civil war: more than 100 people were injured by a chlorine attack in aleppo tuesday. one person is killed by the blast of barrel bombs.
